text: Margrethe Vestager (; born 13 April 1968) is a Danish politician. She is a European Commissioner in the Ursula von der Leyen Commission. She is the Executive Vice President of the European Commission for A Europe Fit for the Digital Age since December 2019 and European Commissioner for Competition since 2014. Vestager is a member of the Danish Social Liberal Party. ==Notes== ==References== Category:1968 births Category:Living people Category:European Union politicians Category:Danish politicians
